### MCP + Copilot API Examples
### Start via AppHost (starts both McpServer and McpApi together)
@mcpApiHost = http://localhost:5300

### ─── Tool Discovery ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### List all tools discovered from the MCP server
### Shows tool names, descriptions, and the MCP server endpoint
GET {{mcpApiHost}}/api/mcp/tools

### ─── MCP-Backed Chat ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Create a Copilot session backed by MCP tools
### The response includes availableTools — all MCP tools are pre-loaded
# @name mcpSession
POST {{mcpApiHost}}/api/mcp/sessions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "model": "gpt-4o"
}

###

@mcpSessionId = {{mcpSession.response.body.sessionId}}

### Ask about weather — Copilot will call get_weather via MCP
POST {{mcpApiHost}}/api/mcp/{{mcpSessionId}}/messages
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "What's the weather like in London and Tokyo right now? Compare them."
}

###

### Use the calculator tool — Copilot will call calculate via MCP
POST {{mcpApiHost}}/api/mcp/{{mcpSessionId}}/messages
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "What is 17 * 23 + sqrt(144)? Show the calculation steps."
}

###

### Use the time tool — Copilot will call get_current_time via MCP
POST {{mcpApiHost}}/api/mcp/{{mcpSessionId}}/messages
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "What time is it right now in New York, London, and Tokyo?"
}

###

### Multi-tool call — Copilot orchestrates multiple MCP tool calls
POST {{mcpApiHost}}/api/mcp/{{mcpSessionId}}/messages
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "message": "I'm planning a trip. Give me the weather in Dubai and the current time there. Also, what's 15% of 2500 for tipping budget?"
}

###

### Delete the MCP session
DELETE {{mcpApiHost}}/api/mcp/{{mcpSessionId}}
